sql: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T2.pilot_name), T1.location FROM Hangar AS T1 JOIN PilotSkills AS T2 ON T1.plane_name = T2.plane_name WHERE T2.age < 30 GROUP BY T1.location ORDER BY COUNT(DISTINCT T2.pilot_name) DESC
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.plane_name) FROM PilotSkills AS T1 GROUP BY T1.age HAVING COUNT(T1.plane_name) > 1 AND T1.age != 50

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.plane_name), COUNT(T3.location) FROM PilotSkills AS T1 JOIN Hangar AS T2 ON T1.plane_name = T2.plane_name JOIN Hangar AS T3 ON T1.plane_name = T3.plane_name WHERE T1.age > 30 OR T2.location IN (SELECT location FROM Hangar WHERE location = 'New York')
SELECT COUNT(plane_name) FROM PilotSkills WHERE age <= 30
SELECT SUM(T1.age), T2.location, COUNT(T1.plane_name) FROM PilotSkills AS T1 JOIN Hangar AS T2 ON T1.plane_name = T2.plane_name WHERE T1.age >= 40 LIMIT 10

SELECT T1.plane_name, MIN(T1.age) FROM PilotSkills AS T1 WHERE T1.pilot_name = 'John' AND EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM Hangar AS T2 WHERE T1.plane_name = T2.plane_name AND T2.location = 'New York') GROUP BY T1.plane_name
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.pilot_name), T2.location FROM PilotSkills AS T1 JOIN Hangar AS T2 ON T1.plane_name = T2.plane_name WHERE T1.age = 50 LIMIT 10
SELECT T1.plane_name, T1.age, T2.location FROM PilotSkills AS T1 JOIN Hangar AS T2 ON T1.plane_name = T2.plane_name WHERE T1.age >= 30 ORDER BY T1.age DESC
SELECT pilot_name FROM PilotSkills WHERE age > 30 GROUP BY age
SELECT T1.plane_name, SUM(T1.age) FROM PilotSkills AS T1 JOIN Hangar AS T2 ON T1.plane_name = T2.plane_name GROUP BY T1.plane_name HAVING SUM(T1.age) > 50
SELECT T1.pilot_name FROM PilotSkills AS T1 JOIN Hangar AS T2 ON T1.plane_name = T2.plane_name WHERE T1.age > (SELECT AVG(age) FROM PilotSkills)

SELECT T1.pilot_name, COUNT(DISTINCT T2.location) FROM PilotSkills AS T1 JOIN Hangar AS T2 ON T1.plane_name = T2.plane_name WHERE T1.age > 40 OR T1.plane_name NOT IN (SELECT plane_name FROM Hangar WHERE location = 'New York') ORDER BY T1.pilot_name DESC LIMIT 10

SELECT T1.pilot_name, T2.location, SUM(T1.age) FROM PilotSkills AS T1 JOIN Hangar AS T2 ON T1.plane_name = T2.plane_name WHERE T1.age BETWEEN 30 AND 40 AND T1.pilot_name = 'John' GROUP BY T2.location HAVING SUM(T1.age) > 100
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.plane_name) FROM PilotSkills AS T1 JOIN Hangar AS T2 ON T1.plane_name = T2.plane_name WHERE T2.location < 'New York' ORDER BY T1.age DESC
SELECT T1.pilot_name FROM PilotSkills AS T1 JOIN Hangar AS T2 ON T1.plane_name = T2.plane_name WHERE T1.age > 30 OR T2.location = 'New York' ORDER BY T1.age DESC
SELECT T1.pilot_name, T2.pilot_name FROM PilotSkills AS T1 JOIN PilotSkills AS T2 ON T1.plane_name = T2.plane_name WHERE T1.age > 50 AND T1.pilot_name = 'John'
SELECT T1.pilot_name, T2.location FROM PilotSkills AS T1 JOIN Hangar AS T2 ON T1.plane_name = T2.plane_name ORDER BY T1.age ASC
SELECT T1.age, AVG(T1.age) FROM (SELECT T2.age, T2.plane_name FROM PilotSkills AS T2 WHERE T2.plane_name IN (SELECT plane_name FROM Hangar)) AS T1 GROUP BY T1.age
SELECT T1.pilot_name, AVG(T1.age) FROM PilotSkills AS T1 JOIN Hangar AS T2 ON T1.plane_name = T2.plane_name WHERE T1.age <= 40 GROUP BY T1.pilot_name LIMIT 5

SELECT T1.pilot_name, T1.plane_name FROM PilotSkills AS T1 JOIN PilotSkills AS T2 ON T1.plane_name = T2.plane_name WHERE T1.age BETWEEN 30 AND 40 OR T1.age > 50 OR EXISTS (SELECT * FROM Hangar WHERE location = 'New York' AND plane_name = T1.plane_name) ORDER BY T1.pilot_name ASC

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.plane_name), COUNT(T1.age) FROM PilotSkills AS T1 JOIN Hangar AS T2 ON T1.plane_name = T2.plane_name WHERE T2.location = 'New York' AND T1.age > 30 ORDER BY T1.age ASC LIMIT 10
